<SUBHEAD>
Sharif Appeals Hijacking Conviction
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) -- Ousted Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif today appealed
a life sentence from hijacking and terrorism convictions. An anti-terrorist
court last week found Sharif guilty of hijacking and terrorism but acquitted him
of attempted murder and kidnapping on Oct. 12, the day his dismissal of Gen.
Pervez Musharraf caused the army to seize power in Pakistan. Sharif was accused
of refusing to let a passenger airliner carrying Musharraf and 197 others land
in Karachi.
</P>
