Hearing Reopens for U.S. Soldier
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   VILSECK, Germany (AP) -- A U.S. Army sergeant accused of raping and killing
an 11-year-old girl while stationed in Kosovo faced another hearing today to
determine if he will be court-martialed. It is the first time a peacekeeper from
any country has been accused of such serious crimes since the 50,000-strong
NATO-led force entered the Yugoslav province June 12. Staff Sgt. Frank J.
Ronghi, 35, originally was charged with premeditated murder and indecent acts
