<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   Glen Campbell's ''Wichita Lineman'' was among 49 recordings
inducted into the music industry's Hall of Fame this year.
Campbell, who was born on April 22, 1936, is proud of his guitar
playing on the song. '''Wichita Lineman' has more chords than 25
country songs,'' he said in an interview. ''Most country acts who
sing it don't play along, they just strum.''
</P>
<P>
   Comedian-actor Martin Lawrence says he had to learn how to walk
again after his near-death collapse while jogging last August.
''You go under, your functions, everything, shuts down. I had to
learn to walk again. All kinds of stuff. It was a real traumatic
experience,'' he told ''Entertainment Tonight,'' a syndicated TV
show. Lawrence collapsed while jogging in heavy clothing in
100-degree heat. He was trying to lose weight for a movie. Lawrence
was born on April 16, 1965.
</P>
<P>
   Andie MacDowell says the best part of being an actress is trying
to understand what motivates people. That's what she told fans at
the Cathedral of All Souls, an historic Asheville, N.C., church
where she is a parishioner and is known by her real name Rose
Qualley. ''The fun part is you get to study people. You understand
why people act the way they do, and you have compassion for them,''
said MacDowell, who starred in ''Groundhog Day'' and ''Four
Weddings and a Funeral.'' MacDowell was born on April 21, 1958. She
has a home in the Asheville area.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays April 16-22:
</P>
<P>
   April 16: Singer Bobby Vinton is 65. Actress Ellen Barkin is 46.
Singer Jimmy Osmond is 37. Singer David Pirner of Soul Asylum is
36. Actor-comedian Martin Lawrence is 35. Actor Jon Cryer is 35.
Musician Dan Rieser of Marcy Playground is 34. Actor Lukas Haas is
24.
</P>
