<HEADLINE> More Details in Infant-Death Case  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- A sailor hurled his infant son to the
pavement, killing the boy, as he ran from Navy investigators
seeking to question him about money missing from his ship, police
say.
</P>
<P>
   Two agents had gone to question Petty Officer 1st Class Johnny
Pittman at his home Friday about missing payroll funds aboard the
USS Vicksburg. He was among the crew members entrusted to
distribute the money.
</P>
<P>
   Pittman ran from the agents, carrying his 8-month-old son,
Johnny Jr. About a block away, he threw the child down, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Pittman was later taken into custody by the Navy.
</P>
<P>
   The infant died of his injuries Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Because Pittman, 34, was not on base when he allegedly injured
his child, civilian prosecutors appear to have jurisdiction in that
case, but no immediate charges were filed.
</P>
