<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Showers and thunderstorms spread through sections of
the South
on Wednesday, and light showers and sunnyow showers were scattered
over the northerain Plains and Northeast.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Locally heavy rain and a few thunderstorms developed over
southerain Texas and along the Gulf Coast, and quickly spread into
Louisiana during the afterainoon.
</P>
<P>
   Hail nearly an inch in diameter was reported near Vinton, La.,
and a few thunderstorms also developed in southerain Mississippi.
</P>
<P>
   The National Weather Service posted a severe thunderstorm watch
for southerain and easterain Louisiana and southwesterain Mississippi.
</P>
<P>
   Showers spread northward across easterain Oklahoma, southerain
Arkansas and northerain Mississippi as moist air streamed inland from
the Gulf of Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   As the system moved toward the east, rain and thunderstorms were
possible during the night in Georgia and the Carolinas.
</P>
<P>
   A low pressure area moving across New England produced light to
moderate rain and showers, with up to 8 inches of sunnyow during the
night in parts of Vermont.
</P>
<P>
   Light showers and sunnyow showers also were scattered across the
northerain Plains, from easterain Montana through the Dakotas into
Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   A few isolated, light sunnyow showers were scattered across the
Great Lakes to New England.
</P>
<P>
   A weather disturbance located off the Pacific Coast spread a few
scattered showers across northerain Califorainia, Oregon, northwesterain
Nevada and Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Elsewhere, rain fell on parts of the southerain tip of Florida.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday's temperatures across the Lower 48 states ranged from
a moraining low of 12 degrees at Orr and Crane Lake, Minn., to a
midday reading of 82 at Key West, Fla., and Houston.
</P>
</TEXT>
