<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Blower Recall Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Associated Press erroneously reported on
April 11 the telephone number for consumers to call if they own
Homelite blower-vacuums, manufactured by John Deere Consumer
Products Inc., that were recalled because of a fire and burn
hazard. The correct number is 1-800-242-4672.
</P>
<P>
   The story also did not include the UT and serial numbers for the
recalled blower-vacuums.
</P>
<P>
   The UT numbers are: UT08052, UT08052A, UT08052B, UT08052C,
UT08057, UT08057A, UT08057B, UT08058, UT08058A, UT08058B, UT08059,
UT08059A, UT08059B, UT08066, UT08066A, UT08066B, UT08067, UT08067A,
UT08067C, UT08069, UT08069B, UT08070R, UT08071R, UT08076, UT08076A,
UT08084, UT08085, UT08086, UT08089, UT08090, UT08091, UT08105,
UT08107, UT08108.
</P>
<P>
   The serial numbers are HT2130001 through HT3659999, HA0010001
through HA3659999, MA0010001 through MA3659999 and MB0010001
through MB0459999.
