<HEADLINE> J.P. Morgan Earnings Rise 5 Percent  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Shares of J.P. Morgan rose 3 percent Wednesday
after the investment bank reported that first-quarter profits
increased 5 percent, helped by strong performances in stock and
bond underwriting and other advisory services.
</P>
<P>
   Net income for the three months ended March 31 totaled $628
million, or $3.37 a share, blowing past analysts' expectations of
$2.81 a share.
</P>
<P>
   In the first quarter last year, the New York-based J.P. Morgan
earned $600 million, or $3.01 per share.
</P>
<P>
   Investors bid up the price of J.P. Morgan's shares by $1.93} to
$136.68} in trading Wednesday at 4:30 p.m. on the New York Stock
Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   ''We continued to reap the benefits of our strategic investments
this quarter,'' chairman Douglas A. Warner III said in a statement.
''Strength in equities, investment banking, and asset management
drove growth and has created a much more diversified earnings
mix.''
</P>
<P>
   Total revenues were $2.84 billion in the first quarter, up 14
percent from $2.49 billion for the same period a year ago. The
firm's investment banking business led the way, posting a 41
percent jump in revenues in the period.
</P>
