<HEADLINE> Tax Deadline Is April 17 This Year  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   This year's tax filing deadline for most of America
is Monday,
April 17, instead of the usual April 15. That's because April 15
falls on a Saturday this year, not a normal business day.
<TEXT>
<P>
   People in Massachusetts, Connecticut, Maine, New Hampshire,
Rhode Island, Vermont and most of New York outside of the New York
City area have yet another day, April 18, because of the annual
Patriot's Day holiday on April 17. These returns have to go to the
IRS service centers in either Andover, Mass., -- where Patriot's Day
is a legal holiday -- or Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   The IRS decided it would be easiest to simply allow all those
northeast filers another day.
</P>
<P>
   In New York, April 18 doesn't apply to New York City and Nassau,
Rockland, Suffolk and Westchester counties.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
