<HEADLINE> Facts About Sister O'Laughlin  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Facts about Sister Jeanne O'Laughlin, who played host
Wednesday
to a meeting between Attorney General Janet Reno and Elian
Gonzalez's Miami relatives.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Name: Sister Jeanne O'Laughlin
</P>
<P>
   Born: May 4, 1929
</P>
<P>
   Career: Sister in the Roman Catholic Dominican order; president
of Barry University for 18 years.
</P>
<P>
   Community involvement: Volunteered to help 600 Haitian imigrants
acclimate to Miami when they were released from an Immigration and
Naturalization Service detention center, taking repsonsibility for
about half of them; intervened on behalf of Chinese and Romanian
immigrants, enrolling some at Barry and helping others find jobs at
the school; worked on the Summit of the Americas at Miami
International Airport.
</P>
<P>
   Involvement in Elian Gonzalez case:
</P>
<P>
   --Jan. 26: Played host to meeting between Elian and his
grandmothers.
</P>
<P>
   --Jan. 27: After saying she was neutral in the dispute, changed
to saying she believes boy should stay in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   --Jan. 28: Appeals to Reno in Washington to grant the boy
citizenship.
</P>
<P>
   --Feb. 20: Says she changed her position about Elian after
learning his grandmothers wanted to defect.
</P>
<P>
   --April 11: Invites Elian and family of great-uncle Lazaro
Gonzalez to her house, which becomes site of meeting with Reno.
</P>
</TEXT>
