Tokyo Stocks Fall
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stocks fell Thursday as overnight drops on Wall Street
dragged down Japanese high-technology issues. The Nikkei Stock Average shed
226.95 points to 20,606.26. On Wall Street Wednesday, the Nasdaq plummeted
286.69 points to 3,769.21, while the Down fell 161.95 to 11,125.13.
