<HEADLINE> Boat Sinks Near Philippines; 56 Die  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ZAMBOANGA, Philippines (AP) -- An overloaded wooden ferry boat
capsized, killing at least 56 people, officials said Thursday. More
than 100 others were missing and feared dead.
</P>
<P>
   Abdu Sakur, the governor of southern Sulu province, said the
ferry Arlahada capsized shortly after leaving the capital of the
province, Jolo, Wednesday night. The ferry was headed for the
Philippine province of Tawi Tawi and then to Saba in Malaysia, he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Nineteen people were rescued, he said.
</P>
<P>
   There were no immediate reports of whether foreigners were on
board.
</P>
</TEXT>
