<HEADLINE> Citadel Gets Female Voting Member  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) -- A woman was approved by the state
Legislature on Wednesday to take a seat on the board of The
Citadel, making her the first voting female member of the military
school's governing body.
</P>
<P>
   Lawmakers approved Allison Dean Wright, 35, for one of two open
seats on the board. Wright received a graduate degree in business
from the school's evening college in 1993.
</P>
<P>
   As an advisory member since 1997, Wright was able to discuss
ideas but not vote on them. ''Now I'll know I'll be able to make
difference,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   W. Henry Johnson Junior won the second seat. They replace Jimmy
Jones, who chaired the board during the fight to keep women out of
the military school, and current Chairman Frank Mood.
</P>
<P>
   The formerly all-male corps of cadets graduated its first woman
last year. There are about 60 women cadets at the school now.
</P>
<P>
   The Citadel dropped its all-male admissions policy in 1996,
after the U.S. Supreme Court struck down a similar policy at
Virginia Military Institute.
</P>
</TEXT>
